WEBVTT

00:00:00.566 --> 00:00:02.100
The cotton cemí

00:00:02.733 --> 00:00:06.466
was exceptionally preserved inside a cave

00:00:07.066 --> 00:00:10.800
a cave located near the town of Petitrou

00:00:11.133 --> 00:00:14.400
in the Enriquillo region of the Dominican Republic

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:16.700
a manuscript

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.666
written by Rodolfo Cambiaso Sosa in 1906

00:00:22.066 --> 00:00:23.533
and today preserved

00:00:23.733 --> 00:00:26.800
in the archives of the Smithsonian Institution

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:27.800
in Washington

00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:31.500
documents this exceptional discovery

00:00:31.766 --> 00:00:33.566
and also its acquisition

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:37.066
the manuscript tells of a hunter

00:00:37.466 --> 00:00:40.100
who found the cemí in the cave

00:00:40.333 --> 00:00:42.133
and was so frightened

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:44.533
that he struck it with his machete

00:00:44.966 --> 00:00:48.700
leaving a mark still visible today on its head

00:00:49.466 --> 00:00:51.000
and moreover, the manuscript

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:54.733
says that in 1882

00:00:55.266 --> 00:00:57.133
Giovanni Battista Cambiaso

00:00:57.600 --> 00:00:59.166
Rodolfo’s father

00:00:59.533 --> 00:01:02.100
purchased this object

00:01:02.566 --> 00:01:05.566
bringing it to his home in Santo Domingo

00:01:06.066 --> 00:01:08.600
who was Giovanni Battista Cambiaso?

00:01:08.866 --> 00:01:10.400
he is an important figure

00:01:11.333 --> 00:01:12.733
in Dominican history

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:15.166
he was of Genoese origin

00:01:15.666 --> 00:01:16.466
and

00:01:16.933 --> 00:01:18.933
is listed among the co-founders

00:01:19.466 --> 00:01:21.366
of the Dominican Navy

00:01:21.966 --> 00:01:24.000
he was also the first consul of the

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:26.566
Kingdom of Sardinia in Santo Domingo

00:01:26.733 --> 00:01:29.166
and the first Italian consul

00:01:29.933 --> 00:01:34.933
he died in 1886, leaving his collection

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:37.466
of Taíno antiquities

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:39.000
to his son Rodolfo
